  "prompt": "Which is the best app to track markets?",
  "response": "The \"best\" app to track markets can vary depending on your specific needs and preferences. However, here are some popular options that are widely regarded for their features and user experience:\n\n1. **Yahoo Finance**: Offers real-time stock quotes, news, and customizable watchlists. It has a user-friendly interface and provides comprehensive market analysis.\n\n2. **Bloomberg**: Known for its in-depth financial analysis and news coverage. The app offers a wealth of data on stocks, commodities, currencies, and more.\n\n3. **TradingView**: Excellent for both beginners and experienced traders, it provides interactive charts, social networking features, and a wide range of technical analysis tools.\n\n4. **MarketWatch**: Offers market news, data, and portfolio tracking. It's comprehensive and also provides analysis and articles that can help users stay informed.\n\n5. **TD Ameritrade Mobile**: Ideal for those who have an account with TD Ameritrade, this app provides powerful trading tools, research reports, and real-time data.\n\n6. **Robinhood**: While primarily a trading app, it also allows users to track stocks and markets in real time. It is especially popular among younger investors.\n\n7. **Investing.com**: This app provides a comprehensive suite of tools, including live quotes, charts, economic calendars, and news updates for various markets.\n\n8. **CoinMarketCap**: If you're specifically interested in cryptocurrency markets, this app is very informative and provides real-time data on a vast number of cryptocurrencies.\n\nWhen choosing an app, consider factors such as ease of use, the features you need, the types of markets you're interested in, and whether you want trading capabilities or just market tracking.",
